skills.name: Nynorsk
skills.tipsAndNotes:
###Nynorsk

Nynorsk (literally, "New Norwegian") is a literary form of Norwegian, based on country dialects and constructed in the 19th century to serve as a national language more clearly distinct from Danish than Bokml.

The standard language was originally created by Ivar Aasen during the mid-19th century, to provide a Norwegian alternative to the Danish language which was commonly written in Norway at the time.

27% of Norwegian municipalities have declared Nynorsk as their official language form, and these areas account for about 12% of the Norwegian population. The vast majority of the Norwegian population writes in Bokml, which is taught in all other lessons of the course.
